owing two parallel lines: $\\frac{x-1}{5}=\\frac{y+2}{3}=z$ and $\\frac{x+3}{5}=\\frac{y-4}{3}=z-1$:#{1}":[101,130],"#Practice:#Find the distance from the point $(1,1,-1)$ to the line of intersection of the planes $x+y+z = 1$ and $2x-y-5z=1$:":[131,192],"#Practice:#Find the distance from the point $(1,1,-1)$ to the line of intersection of the planes $x+y+z = 1$ and $2x-y-5z=1$:#{1}":[133,192],"#Practice:#Two vertices of a triangle are $(6,-1)$ and $(-2,5)$. If the orthocenter (intersection of altitudes) of the triangle is at $(1,2)$, find the coordinates of the third vertex:":[193,214],"#Practice:#Two vertices of a triangle are $(6,-1)$ and $(-2,5)$. If the orthocenter (intersection of altitudes) of the triangle is at $(1,2)$, find the coordinates of the third vertex:#{1}":[195,195],"#Practice:#Two vertices of a triangle are $(6,-1)$ and $(-2,5)$. If the orthocenter (intersection of altitudes) of the triangle is at $(1,2)$, find the coordinates of the third vertex:#{2}":[196,196],"#Practice:#Two vertices of a triangle are $(6,-1)$ and $(-2,5)$. If the orthocenter (intersection of altitudes) of the triangle is at $(1,2)$, find the coordinates of the third vertex:#{3}":[197,197],"#Practice:#Two vertices of a triangle are $(6,-1)$ and $(-2,5)$. If the orthocenter (intersection of altitudes) of the triangle is at $(1,2)$, find the coordinates of the third vertex:#{4}":[198,198],"#Practice:#Two vertices of a triangle are $(6,-1)$ and $(-2,5)$. If the orthocenter (intersection of altitudes) of the triangle is at $(1,2)$, find the coordinates of the third vertex:#{5}":[199,199],"#Practice:#Two vertices of a triangle are $(6,-1)$ and $(-2,5)$. If the orthocenter (intersection of altitudes) of the triangle is at $(1,2)$, find the coordinates of the third vertex:#{6}":[200,214],"#Practice:#In a regular tetrahedron $ABCD$, find the coordinates of the point $M$ in the basis $\\{A,AD,AB,AC\\}$, if the point $M$ has coordinates $(\\frac{1}{3},\\frac{1}{3},\\frac{1}{3})$ in the basis $\\{D,DA,DB,DC\\}$.":[215,237],"#Practice:#In a regular tetrahedron $ABCD$, find the coordinates of the point $M$ in the basis $\\{A,AD,AB,AC\\}$, if the point $M$ has coordinates $(\\frac{1}{3},\\frac{1}{3},\\frac{1}{3})$ in the basis $\\{D,DA,DB,DC\\}$.#{1}":[217,220],"#Practice:#In a regular tetrahedron $ABCD$, find the coordinates of the point $M$ in the basis $\\{A,AD,AB,AC\\}$, if the point $M$ has coordinates $(\\frac{1}{3},\\frac{1}{3},\\frac{1}{3})$ in the basis $\\{D,DA,DB,DC\\}$.#{2}":[221,221],"#Practice:#In a regular tetrahedron $ABCD$, find the coordinates of the point $M$ in the basis $\\{A,AD,AB,AC\\}$, if the point $M$ has coordinates $(\\frac{1}{3},\\frac{1}{3},\\frac{1}{3})$ in the basis $\\{D,DA,DB,DC\\}$.#{3}":[222,222],"#Practice:#In a regular tetrahedron $ABCD$, find the coordinates of the point $M$ in the basis $\\{A,AD,AB,AC\\}$, if the point $M$ has coordinates $(\\frac{1}{3},\\frac{1}{3},\\frac{1}{3})$ in the basis $\\{D,DA,DB,DC\\}$.#{4}":[223,224],"#Practice:#In a regular tetrahedron $ABCD$, find the coordinates of the point $M$ in the basis $\\{A,AD,AB,AC\\}$, if the point $M$ has coordinates $(\\frac{1}{3},\\frac{1}{3},\\frac{1}{3})$ in the basis $\\{D,DA,DB,DC\\}$.#{5}":[225,237]},"outlinks":[],"metadata":{"tags":["#1stYear"]},"task_lines":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"1895n6f","at":1761996506065}},"smart_blocks:Midterm 2 - AGLA.md#Theory:": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.04252266,-0.0419703,0.0234535,-0.03473336,-0.08537456,0.01711354,-0.01057996,0.061062,0.05465872,-0.00024143,0.03921971,-0.07160738,0.04840165,0.05912562,0.01261313,-0.01624936,-0.02160533,0.08367623,-0.0816339,0.02776253,0.07417446,-0.0247575,-0.02039753,-0.04738717,0.10049915,0.07483776,0.01249307,0.00378438,-0.01291756,-0.25743902,0.04721101,0.09059177,0.00160451,0.01642774,-0.0189513,-0.01645094,-0.02899579,0.02620323,-0.0430698,-0.02791495,0.02634392,0.00822536,0.0175304,-0.08510847,-0.06511941,-0.0112281,-0.0548669,0.02330432,-0.06